                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/36</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Collector
                            <persName type="to">Cobb</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ascertain whether Watson and companions requested military escort or guard for
                    their trip from Chihuahua to Cusihuiriachic. If so, did authorities refuse to
                    furnish escort or guard? Also ascertain <pb facs="0733" n="657" xml:id="pg_657"
                    /> what assurances, if any, Watson and companions had received from Mexican
                    authorities that it would be safe to resume operations at Cusihuiriachic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
